The Research Institute added that the Hungarian Guard's political strategy likely to provoke this situation is the main reason.
As they say, this is explained by one of the main shortcomings of the Hungarian political actors: "public actors have passed the public debate on the Roma case to representatives of the radical and extreme political groups that have based a political strategy on the dispute between the Tzigans and the Hungarians."
The problem is getting worse, normal dialogue becomes impossible, extremists are becoming stronger, and the arrival of aggressive conflicts is more likely, they say.
