The Mifid, which amends the Value Market Act, involves the modernisation of financial markets, as it strengthens investor protection, improves the powers of the Directors of the National Securities Market Commission (NCMV) and promotes cooperation between the various leaders of the European Union.
The new regulation will provide financial consulting services for both specialized social reasons and natural or legal persons and create a new type of financial services (ESIS), financial consulting companies (AFI), which combine value companies, value agencies and portfolio management companies.
In addition, it increases the number of systems for the execution of operations on financial instruments, so that it is possible to add to regulated secondary markets multilateral trading systems and internationalization systems, which face competition with current stock exchange managers.
The Act also obliges investment services undertakings to disclose on the market information on key aspects of their business profile, exposure to risk and risk management and requires them to keep a record of all their operations in order to facilitate the control of the NCMV.
